      "The optional memorial 'Saint Apollinaris, Bishop and Martyr' has been added on July 20th since the year 2002 (<a href=\"https://press.vatican.va/content/salastampa/it/bollettino/pubblico/2002/03/22/0150/00449.html\" target=\"_blank\">Vatican Press conference: Presentation of the Editio Typica Tertia of the Roman Missal</a>), applicable to the year 2026.",
      "The optional memorial 'Saint Sharbel Makhluf, Hermit' has been added on July 24th since the year 2002 (<a href=\"https://press.vatican.va/content/salastampa/it/bollettino/pubblico/2002/03/22/0150/00449.html\" target=\"_blank\">Vatican Press conference: Presentation of the Editio Typica Tertia of the Roman Missal</a>), applicable to the year 2026.",
      "The optional memorial 'Saint Peter Julian Eymard, Priest', added in the Editio Typica Tertia 2002 of the Roman Missal since the year 2002 (<a href=\"https://press.vatican.va/content/salastampa/it/bollettino/pubblico/2002/03/22/0150/00449.html\" target=\"_blank\">Vatican Press conference: Presentation of the Editio Typica Tertia of the Roman Missal</a>) and usually celebrated on August 2nd, is suppressed by the Sunday '18th Sunday of Ordinary Time' in the year 2026.",
      "The optional memorial 'Saint Teresa Benedicta of the Cross, Virgin and Martyr', added in the Editio Typica Tertia 2002 of the Roman Missal since the year 2002 (<a href=\"https://press.vatican.va/content/salastampa/it/bollettino/pubblico/2002/03/22/0150/00449.html\" target=\"_blank\">Vatican Press conference: Presentation of the Editio Typica Tertia of the Roman Missal</a>) and usually celebrated on August 9th, is suppressed by the Sunday '19th Sunday of Ordinary Time' in the year 2026.",
